{"title":"Pole Voima 190mm travel eMTB lives and breathes the “more is more” philosophy","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/25/pole-voima-190mm-travel-emtb-lives-and-breathes-the-more-is-more-philosophy/","date":1624644575000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Pole Bicycles have released the all-new Voima eMTB with a whopping 190mm of front and rear wheel travel. Voima is Finnish for Power, and this enduro eMTB has no shortage of that. A 725 Wh battery fuels a Brose S-MAG motor that delivers up to 90Nm of torque to the rear wheel of this CNC machined aluminium frame. Here’s a brief introduction to one of the biggest eMTBs of 2021, the Pole Voima.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/b-aBEZn7jV4?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" ezoid=\"0.15375446616242772\"></iframe></span></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135227/pole-voima-emtb-silver-190mm-travel.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135227/pole-voima-emtb-silver-190mm-travel.jpg\" alt=\"pole voima emtb brose s-mag motor 725 wh battery 190mm travel\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135227/pole-voima-emtb-silver-190mm-travel.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135227/pole-voima-emtb-silver-190mm-travel-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135227/pole-voima-emtb-silver-190mm-travel-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135227/pole-voima-emtb-silver-190mm-travel-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135227/pole-voima-emtb-silver-190mm-travel-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135227/pole-voima-emtb-silver-190mm-travel-696x464.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135227/pole-voima-emtb-silver-190mm-travel-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135227/pole-voima-emtb-silver-190mm-travel-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\"></a></p><p>Like all Pole Bicycles, the Pole Voima eMTB is manufactured in-house in Finland. This is their first foray into the world of electric mountain bikes, and boy have they made an entrance. The Voima is massive in almost every sense of the word; massive battery, massive power, massive travel and massively generous reach figures.</p><ul><li>Intention: Enduro eMTB Riding and Racing</li><li>Fork Travel: 190mm</li><li>Rear Wheel Travel: 190mm</li><li>Wheel Size: 29″</li><li>Frame Sizes: K1-K4</li></ul><figure id=\"attachment_263027\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-263027\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25134002/pole-voima-frame-emtb-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25134002/pole-voima-frame-emtb-1.jpg\" alt=\"pole voima emtb frameset bzw battery\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25134002/pole-voima-frame-emtb-1.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25134002/pole-voima-frame-emtb-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25134002/pole-voima-frame-emtb-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25134002/pole-voima-frame-emtb-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25134002/pole-voima-frame-emtb-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25134002/pole-voima-frame-emtb-1-696x464.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25134002/pole-voima-frame-emtb-1-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25134002/pole-voima-frame-emtb-1-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-263027\">The Voima’s 725 Wh BZW battery inserts into the downtube from above; the Brose S-Mag Motor sits inside a sealed shell</figcaption></figure><p>Though not exactly cheap by anyone’s standard, the only thing it isn’t massive on is price. The Pole Voima frameset retails at an introductory price of €5,490, with complete bikes starting at €8,490. The bikes aren’t due until early 2022, but you can reserve one now for just €200. Budgeting aside, let’s dig into the frame details.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135209/pole-voima-brose-s-mag-motor-sealed.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135209/pole-voima-brose-s-mag-motor-sealed.jpg\" alt=\"pole voima brose s-mag motor 90Nm torque\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135209/pole-voima-brose-s-mag-motor-sealed.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135209/pole-voima-brose-s-mag-motor-sealed-297x167.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135209/pole-voima-brose-s-mag-motor-sealed-800x450.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135209/pole-voima-brose-s-mag-motor-sealed-120x68.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135209/pole-voima-brose-s-mag-motor-sealed-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135209/pole-voima-brose-s-mag-motor-sealed-696x392.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135209/pole-voima-brose-s-mag-motor-sealed-1068x601.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135209/pole-voima-brose-s-mag-motor-sealed-747x420.jpg 747w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\"></a></p><p>Save for the CNC finish hallmarks of a Pole Bicycle, the Voima looks almost nothing like the Stamina and Evolink enduro bikes. That’s thanks to the all-new SENSEI suspension platform with elevated seatstays that allow room for the motor. This is a four bar linkage with a Virtual Pivot Point that hovers just above the chainline.</p><p>Pole say this layout delivers a progressive leverage ratio and a falling rate of anti-squat to keep pedal feedback to a minimum. Importantly, Pole’s early prototypes of the Voima were put together without the motor. That’s because they wanted to be sure they had a solid pedaling platform with suspension that worked well even without the extra weight of a battery and motor (which tends to improve the overall performance of suspension, in general).</p><figure id=\"attachment_263040\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-263040\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135221/pole-voima-emtb-rear-end.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135221/pole-voima-emtb-rear-end.jpg\" alt=\"pole voima emtb stiff rear end boost double row bearings\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135221/pole-voima-emtb-rear-end.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135221/pole-voima-emtb-rear-end-297x167.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135221/pole-voima-emtb-rear-end-800x450.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135221/pole-voima-emtb-rear-end-120x68.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135221/pole-voima-emtb-rear-end-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135221/pole-voima-emtb-rear-end-696x392.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135221/pole-voima-emtb-rear-end-1068x601.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135221/pole-voima-emtb-rear-end-747x420.jpg 747w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-263040\">The Pole Voima swingarm runs a boost (148mm x 12mm) rear end with double row bearings bringing the necessary stiffness</figcaption></figure><p>The swingarm itself lacks a traditional seatstay bridge. Pole say that the double row bearings employed make the rear end more than stiff enough.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135233/pole-voima-emtb-zeb-fork-190mm-travel.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135233/pole-voima-emtb-zeb-fork-190mm-travel.jpg\" alt=\"pole voima emtb long low slack geometry\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135233/pole-voima-emtb-zeb-fork-190mm-travel.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135233/pole-voima-emtb-zeb-fork-190mm-travel-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135233/pole-voima-emtb-zeb-fork-190mm-travel-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135233/pole-voima-emtb-zeb-fork-190mm-travel-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135233/pole-voima-emtb-zeb-fork-190mm-travel-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135233/pole-voima-emtb-zeb-fork-190mm-travel-696x464.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135233/pole-voima-emtb-zeb-fork-190mm-travel-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135233/pole-voima-emtb-zeb-fork-190mm-travel-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\"></a></p><p>In true Pole Bicycles fashion, the Voima eMTB has some of the most generous reach figures on the market. The range stretches from 450mm in K1 right up to 535mm in K4, serving rider heights from 160cm to over 195cm. A slack head tube sits at 63.5° while the seat tube angle is very upright at 80°.&nbsp;</p><p>The chainstay length is generous too at an effective 455mm across all frame sizes, resulting in some whopping wheelbase figures (1368mm in K4).</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25103133/pole-voima-geometry-chart-190mm-emtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25103133/pole-voima-geometry-chart-190mm-emtb.jpg\" alt=\"pole voima geometry chart 190mm travel alloy emtb\" width=\"1200\" height=\"514\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25103133/pole-voima-geometry-chart-190mm-emtb.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25103133/pole-voima-geometry-chart-190mm-emtb-297x127.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25103133/pole-voima-geometry-chart-190mm-emtb-800x343.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25103133/pole-voima-geometry-chart-190mm-emtb-120x51.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25103133/pole-voima-geometry-chart-190mm-emtb-768x329.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25103133/pole-voima-geometry-chart-190mm-emtb-696x298.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25103133/pole-voima-geometry-chart-190mm-emtb-1068x457.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25103133/pole-voima-geometry-chart-190mm-emtb-981x420.jpg 981w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\"></a>The bonded 7075-T6 aluminum frame is compatible with dual-crown forks, so if you wanted to set it up as your own private shuttle for the bike parks, you can go right ahead and stick a FOX 40 on it.</p><p>For those readers interested in a more complete backstory of the Pole Voima’s development, the following seventeen minute video from Pole will be right up your street.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/YgqCA1T_Vfg?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135215/pole-voima-emtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135215/pole-voima-emtb.jpg\" alt=\"pole voima emtb one footer jump\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135215/pole-voima-emtb.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135215/pole-voima-emtb-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135215/pole-voima-emtb-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135215/pole-voima-emtb-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135215/pole-voima-emtb-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135215/pole-voima-emtb-696x464.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135215/pole-voima-emtb-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135215/pole-voima-emtb-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\"></a></p><p>The Pole Voima isn’t ready to bolt out of the starting blocks just yet. It is still awaiting the industry’s toughest EFBE safety testing in Germany. Assuming that will be successful and the Voima frame passes (as the remastered <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/04/23/pole-bicycles-resolve-to-do-better-dropping-stronger-remastered-stamina-in-true-gold/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Stamina</a> did), production will go ahead this autumn with K2 and K3 framesets available on a limited basis.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135729/pole-voima-emtb-cornering.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135729/pole-voima-emtb-cornering.jpg\" alt=\"pole voima emtb cornering\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135729/pole-voima-emtb-cornering.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135729/pole-voima-emtb-cornering-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135729/pole-voima-emtb-cornering-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135729/pole-voima-emtb-cornering-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135729/pole-voima-emtb-cornering-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135729/pole-voima-emtb-cornering-696x464.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135729/pole-voima-emtb-cornering-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/25135729/pole-voima-emtb-cornering-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\"></a></p><p>Pole have an introductory price for the Voima, set to 5490 € for the frameset with complete builds coming in at 8490 €. Beyond the introductory pricing time frame (no exact dates yet) framesets will be 5990 € and complete builds will be 8990 €.</p><p><a href=\"https://polebicycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>PoleBicycles.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"e77a5d329d51cfd9aa9b1565234ddebb4d0897fa47b542035f544fc65ab242d1","category":"Cycling"}